    thinking: "**Constructing Server Infrastructure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on building the `/server.ts` file. The current tasks involve setting up an Express application with appropriate middleware for CORS and JSON parsing. I\'m also including simple environment variable loading, with a check for the Gemini API key. Finally, the endpoint `/api/travel` will be integrated.\n\n\n**Refining API Endpoint Design**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the `/api/travel` endpoint\'s structure. Thinking of how to format the Gemini response; let\'s render Markdown. We\'ll also add checks for content safety. I\'m focusing on crafting a rich response format including suggested items. Looking at the implementation of `server.ts` based on \"Full-Stack Applications (Express + Vite)\" for guidance on importing express, path, and other libraries and packages.\n\n\n**Expanding API Functionality**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `/api/chat` route. The goal is a unified endpoint that supports not just itinerary generation, but also general Philippines-related Q&A with conversational history! I\'m planning a flexible request body, incorporating both the user\'s message and the chat history. The aim is a rich, multi-turn experience powered by the Gemini model. I\'m exploring the `ai.chats.create` method for elegant chat creation.\n\n\n**Implementing Chat History**\n\nI\'m now integrating the `/api/chat` route to handle both trip planning and general questions. I\'ve added error handling for the Gemini API key and implemented the Gemini chat creation with a `systemInstruction` for Bayani\'s persona. The endpoint is set up to receive both a user\'s message and a chat history array, which is key for conversational flow. I am handling potential errors.\n\n\n"
