    thinking: "**Designing the UI Framework**\n\nI\'m focusing now on building the main user interface in `/src/App.tsx`. I\'ve started breaking down the required modules. First up is the Interactive Geographic Navigator. This should allow the user to select Luzon, Visayas, or Mindanao, displaying a brief description and weather data for each region upon selection.\n\n\n**Refining the Destination Showcase**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the \"Interactive Destination Showcase Card.\" I\'ve added collapsible sections to display more information. I am thinking of adding better imagery to enhance the user experience. The next step will be to finalize the design.\n\n\n**Integrating the Final Components**\n\nI\'m now integrating the final components into the `/src/App.tsx` dashboard. The AI Tour Concierge Chatbot (\"Bayani\") is almost complete, with predefined prompts and markdown formatting. I\'ve also implemented the Bento Info Badges for quick stats. Next, I\'ll incorporate the quiz functionality and Lucide icons for aesthetic layouts.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will write the complete implementation of `/src/App.tsx` using a beautifully styled Bento Grid layout matching the requested theme. This dashboard includes sections for exploring geographic divisions, must-visit destinations with interactive secrets, a culinary explorer, a multi-dialect travel phrasebook, a native trivia challenge, and the Gemini-powered travel concierge chatbot (\"Bayani\")."
